fields.description:
The following is accepted and doesn't cause an error, but setting the app property appropriately has no effect:
{code:java}
"dynamicContentMacros": [
  {
    "condition": "addon_property_equal_to",
    "params": {
      "propertyKey": "prop-key",
      "objectName": "obj-name",
      "value": "true"
    },
    "key": "somemacro",
    "name": {
      "value": "Some Macro"
    },
    "documentation": {
      "url": "https://docs..."
    },
    "url": "/macro/some/some-macro.html",
    "bodyType": "rich-text",
    "icon": {
      "width": 72,
      "height": 72,
      "url": "/icons/somemacro/somemacro.png"
    },
    "cacheable": true,
    "description": {
      "value": "Some Macro"
    }
  },

{code}
Since dynamic modules can't be used without some sort of 'back end', since user invoked code isn't allowed to register them!
